1
00:00:22,366 --> 00:00:24,166
♪ I THINK IT'S TIME
WE BLOW THIS SCENE. ♪

2
00:00:24,166 --> 00:00:27,033
♪ GET EVERYBODY
AND THEIR STUFF TOGETHER. ♪

3
00:00:27,033 --> 00:00:29,733
♪ OK, 3, 2, 1.
LET'S JAM. ♪

4
00:02:01,814 --> 00:02:03,881
CONFIRMED.

5
00:02:04,947 --> 00:02:08,881
TO THE NEW ALLIANCE,
AND PERHAPS EVEN FRIENDSHIP.

6
00:02:08,881 --> 00:02:11,281
AND TO SUCCESS
FOR BOTH OF US.

7
00:02:11,281 --> 00:02:13,881
I HAD NO IDEA
THE VIEW FROM UP HERE

8
00:02:13,881 --> 00:02:15,181
WOULD BE SO BREATHTAKING.

9
00:02:15,181 --> 00:02:16,947
IT MAKES ME SAD TO LEAVE.

10
00:02:16,947 --> 00:02:20,014
THE NEXT TIME,
YOU'LL HAVE TO STAY FOR DINNER.

11
00:02:20,014 --> 00:02:22,114
OUR CHEF COOKS
A CANTONESE CUISINE

12
00:02:22,114 --> 00:02:24,614
THAT'S JUST AS SUPERB
AS THE SCENERY.

13
00:02:24,614 --> 00:02:26,981
IT'S TO DIE FOR,
SO TO SPEAK.

14
00:02:26,981 --> 00:02:29,181
THAT'S QUITE AN INVITATION.

15
00:02:29,181 --> 00:02:31,147
I NEVER THOUGHT
I'D BREAK BREAD WITH A CAPO

16
00:02:31,147 --> 00:02:34,247
FROM THE RED DRAGON CLAN.

17
00:02:34,247 --> 00:02:34,914
DON'T WORRY.

18
00:02:34,914 --> 00:02:36,847
THE FOOD WON'T BE POISONED.

19
00:02:36,847 --> 00:02:39,047
NO MORE BETRAYALS.

20
00:02:47,714 --> 00:02:52,881
THANK GOD I CAN FINALLY RELAX,
TAKE A LITTLE BREATHER.

21
00:02:59,914 --> 00:03:04,347
[BIRD SQUAWKING]

22
00:03:08,347 --> 00:03:10,214
THIS WON'T DO YOU ANY GOOD.

23
00:03:10,214 --> 00:03:12,181
THE TIMES HAVE CHANGED.

24
00:03:12,181 --> 00:03:15,381
THE SYNDICATES CAN'T
SURVIVE LIKE THIS ANY LONGER.

25
00:03:15,381 --> 00:03:19,881
THIS ENDLESS BLOODLETTING
IS TEARING US ALL APART.

26
00:03:23,181 --> 00:03:24,281
[GASPS]

27
00:03:24,281 --> 00:03:31,175
IF SPIKE WERE HERE...
YOU WOULD NEVER HAVE DONE THIS.

28
00:03:45,355 --> 00:03:48,822
I DON'T FEEL UP FOR THIS.

29
00:03:48,822 --> 00:03:49,855
[WHINES]

30
00:03:49,855 --> 00:03:50,688
HUH?

31
00:03:50,688 --> 00:03:53,055
I SAID, I DON'T FEEL
LIKE DOING THIS.

32
00:03:53,055 --> 00:03:54,888
THEN I HAVE NO CHOICE.

33
00:03:54,888 --> 00:03:56,988
HOLD ON A MINUTE, SPIKE.

34
00:03:56,988 --> 00:03:58,922
HEY, I DON'T WANT
TO BOTHER YOU.

35
00:03:58,922 --> 00:04:00,322
DON'T GET SALTY, ALL RIGHT?

36
00:04:00,322 --> 00:04:02,988
JUST HOW MUCH DO YOU
KNOW ABOUT THESE BOYS?

37
00:04:02,988 --> 00:04:05,055
ENOUGH TO GET THE PICTURE.

38
00:04:05,055 --> 00:04:06,222
WELL, THEN?

39
00:04:06,222 --> 00:04:07,255
THERE'S A FAT BOUNTY,

40
00:04:07,255 --> 00:04:10,722
PLENTY OF INFO ON THE GUY,
AND WE HAVE A LEAD.

41
00:04:10,722 --> 00:04:12,655
SO WHAT ARE YOU SCARED OF?

42
00:04:12,655 --> 00:04:15,355
SPIKE, YOU'RE AVOIDING
THE SUBJECT, AND YOU KNOW IT.

43
00:04:15,355 --> 00:04:18,855
WHAT ARE TRYING
TO HIDE FROM ME?

44
00:04:18,855 --> 00:04:21,955
SO HOW'D YOU MESS UP
YOUR ARM, HUH, JET?

45
00:04:21,955 --> 00:04:23,988
WHAT DOES THAT
HAVE TO DO WITH IT?

46
00:04:23,988 --> 00:04:24,988
NOTHING AT ALL.

47
00:04:24,988 --> 00:04:27,755
SO WHEN ARE YOU GOING
TO ANSWER MY QUESTION?

48
00:04:27,755 --> 00:04:30,188
WHEN YOU ANSWER MINE.

49
00:04:33,855 --> 00:04:35,855
WHY IS THIS DOOR SO SMALL?

50
00:04:35,855 --> 00:04:38,188
YOU CAN HARDLY GET THROUGH.

51
00:04:41,022 --> 00:04:42,755
UH, WHAT'S GOING ON?

52
00:04:42,755 --> 00:04:43,922
NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

53
00:04:43,922 --> 00:04:44,888
HMM. HEY!

54
00:04:44,888 --> 00:04:46,888
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
A TEAM HERE, YOU KNOW.

55
00:04:46,888 --> 00:04:48,822
SINCE WHEN?

56
00:04:48,822 --> 00:04:51,422
YOU'RE JUST WALKING TROUBLE,
SO STAY OUT OF IT.

57
00:04:51,422 --> 00:04:53,922
HMM. FINE.

58
00:04:53,922 --> 00:04:55,688
LIKE I CARE.

59
00:04:55,688 --> 00:04:57,688
SO WHO'S THIS GUY? NEW HIT?

60
00:04:57,688 --> 00:04:59,155
ASK BEFORE YOU LOOK.

61
00:04:59,155 --> 00:05:01,088
IT'S SITTING RIGHT THERE.

62
00:05:01,088 --> 00:05:02,322
LIGHTEN UP.

63
00:05:02,322 --> 00:05:03,255
SPIKE!

64
00:05:03,255 --> 00:05:05,688
WAIT A MINUTE, SPIKE!

65
00:05:16,455 --> 00:05:17,888
PREPARE FOR TAKEOFF.

66
00:05:17,888 --> 00:05:19,388
SPIKE! JERK.

67
00:05:19,388 --> 00:05:20,988
I'M NOT GOING TO BACK YOU UP.

68
00:05:20,988 --> 00:05:22,788
YOUR CALL.

69
00:05:29,388 --> 00:05:30,322
DAMN IT!

70
00:05:30,322 --> 00:05:31,955
BULLHEADED.

71
00:05:31,955 --> 00:05:33,022
MAO YENRAI.

72
00:05:33,022 --> 00:05:36,222
A 28 MILLION BOUNTY
FOR MURDERING A CRIME BOSS.

73
00:05:36,222 --> 00:05:38,922
HE'S THE HEAD
OF A SYNDICATE, HUH?

74
00:05:38,922 --> 00:05:39,622
WHOA!

75
00:05:39,622 --> 00:05:42,255
THAT'S WHO YOU GUYS ARE AFTER?

76
00:05:43,022 --> 00:05:44,922
WHAT? YOU HAVE A FIGHT?

77
00:05:44,922 --> 00:05:47,655
CAN IT!
YOU'RE BEING OBNOXIOUS.

78
00:05:47,655 --> 00:05:48,888
HMM. REALLY?

79
00:05:48,888 --> 00:05:51,022
I SAID, CAN IT!

80
00:05:51,022 --> 00:05:54,655
HE CAN DO WHATEVER
THE HELL HE WANTS.

81
00:05:54,655 --> 00:05:57,822
OH, GOD.
MEN ARE SUCH BABIES.

82
00:05:57,822 --> 00:05:59,255
HMM?

83
00:06:01,355 --> 00:06:02,288
ARE YOU THERE, JET?

84
00:06:02,288 --> 00:06:03,988
I'VE GOT SOMETHING BIG!

85
00:06:03,988 --> 00:06:06,022
SOMETHING BIG? HMM.

86
00:06:23,722 --> 00:06:25,255
MADAM, EXCUSE ME.

87
00:06:25,255 --> 00:06:28,322
I NEED TO SEE YOUR TICKET
FOR THE CONCERT, PLEASE.

88
00:06:28,322 --> 00:06:28,988
TICKET?

89
00:06:28,988 --> 00:06:30,055
OH, I DON'T HAVE ANY TICKET.

90
00:06:30,055 --> 00:06:33,822
WELL, THEN I'M AFRAID
I CAN'T LET YOU IN, MADAM.

91
00:06:33,822 --> 00:06:37,255
ALL RIGHT, BUT HE'S GOING
TO BE VERY UNHAPPY WITH YOU.

92
00:06:37,255 --> 00:06:38,155
HUH?

93
00:06:38,155 --> 00:06:41,122
THAT'S RIGHT, HIM.
BALCONY, FIRST BOX.

94
00:06:41,122 --> 00:06:42,922
YOU KNOW WHO.

95
00:06:42,922 --> 00:06:45,722
OH! MAO YENR--

96
00:06:45,722 --> 00:06:47,755
CAN YOU PARK MY ZIPCRAFT?

97
00:06:47,755 --> 00:06:49,055
IT'S OUT FRONT.

98
00:06:49,055 --> 00:06:50,188
THANKS.

99
00:06:50,188 --> 00:06:52,388
OH! MMM.

100
00:06:53,755 --> 00:06:54,955
WHAT MAKES THEM ALL THINK

101
00:06:54,955 --> 00:06:58,255
THEY CAN DO WHATEVER
THE HELL THEY LIKE?

102
00:06:58,255 --> 00:06:59,122
HUH?

103
00:06:59,122 --> 00:07:02,055
THERE'S AN ENCRYPTION
ON THIS THING.

104
00:07:02,055 --> 00:07:03,222
[WHINES]

105
00:07:03,222 --> 00:07:05,255
HMM? YOU WORRIED?

106
00:07:05,255 --> 00:07:06,255
RELAX.

107
00:07:06,255 --> 00:07:10,188
YOU HAVEN'T SEEN
THE DECRYPTION MASTER AT WORK.

108
00:07:10,188 --> 00:07:11,222
YOU SEE?

109
00:07:11,222 --> 00:07:16,255
NOW WE TYPE IN "MAO YENRAI."

110
00:07:16,255 --> 00:07:17,288
SO I WAS RIGHT.

111
00:07:17,288 --> 00:07:18,122
THE BOUNTY'S FOR REAL,

112
00:07:18,122 --> 00:07:21,688
BUT THERE'S A WHOLE LOT
MORE TO IT.

113
00:07:21,688 --> 00:07:25,222
[ORCHESTRA PLAYING]

114
00:07:50,122 --> 00:07:53,922
[MAN SINGING "AVE MARIA"]

115
00:08:03,188 --> 00:08:05,922
IS THIS MR. MAO YENRAI'S BOX?

116
00:08:05,922 --> 00:08:07,955
I LOOKED ALL OVER FOR IT.

117
00:08:07,955 --> 00:08:08,688
ACTUALLY, I--

118
00:08:08,688 --> 00:08:11,255
YES. WE'VE BEEN
WAITING FOR YOU.

119
00:08:11,922 --> 00:08:13,788
[GASPS]

120
00:08:13,788 --> 00:08:14,988
UNH!

121
00:08:14,988 --> 00:08:18,088
WE REQUEST THAT YOU REMAIN
QUIET DURING THE PERFORMANCE.

122
00:08:18,088 --> 00:08:20,088
HMM.

123
00:08:36,855 --> 00:08:38,655
PUT 'EM BACK!

124
00:08:43,188 --> 00:08:45,288
YOU'RE NOT GETTING AWAY!

125
00:08:49,122 --> 00:08:51,322
GET OUT OF MY WAY!

126
00:08:51,322 --> 00:08:52,322
HMM?

127
00:08:52,322 --> 00:08:53,688
HUH?

128
00:08:53,688 --> 00:08:55,655
HEY, GIVE IT BACK,
YOU DUMBASS!

129
00:08:55,655 --> 00:08:56,655
GIMME!

130
00:08:56,655 --> 00:08:59,088
OOH.

131
00:08:59,088 --> 00:09:01,222
REALLY! KIDS THESE DAYS!

132
00:09:01,222 --> 00:09:04,988
I'LL HAND YOU BOTH
OVER TO THE POLICE!

133
00:09:06,322 --> 00:09:07,988
OH, MY DEAR GOD.

134
00:09:07,988 --> 00:09:10,688
HEY.

135
00:09:10,688 --> 00:09:12,422
[KIDS GIGGLE]

136
00:09:12,422 --> 00:09:14,322
UH...

137
00:09:15,388 --> 00:09:16,422
ISN'T IT BAD FOR YOUR HEALTH

138
00:09:16,422 --> 00:09:18,988
TO DRINK IT ALL
IN ONE GULP, ANNIE?

139
00:09:18,988 --> 00:09:19,788
WHAT'S BAD FOR MY HEALTH

140
00:09:19,788 --> 00:09:21,788
IS SEEING YOU
COME BACK TO LIFE.

141
00:09:21,788 --> 00:09:22,988
IT'S A SHOCK TO THE SYSTEM.

142
00:09:22,988 --> 00:09:25,422
HEY, THANKS A LOT
FOR THE WARM WELCOME.

143
00:09:25,422 --> 00:09:27,322
HMM! WHY WELCOME THE DEAD?

144
00:09:27,322 --> 00:09:28,655
IT'S ALL FUTILE.

145
00:09:28,655 --> 00:09:29,855
BUT I'M ALIVE.

146
00:09:29,855 --> 00:09:32,422
NO, YOU'RE NOT.
YOU DIED 3 YEARS AGO.

147
00:09:32,422 --> 00:09:35,288
THAT'S HOW THINGS WORK HERE.

148
00:09:42,355 --> 00:09:44,822
I KNOW WHY
YOU'RE HERE, SPIKE.

149
00:09:44,822 --> 00:09:46,055
HUH?

150
00:09:46,055 --> 00:09:47,955
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE COME UNLESS
YOU NEEDED SOME INFORMATION,

151
00:09:47,955 --> 00:09:49,088
SOMETHING IMPORTANT, RIGHT?

152
00:09:49,088 --> 00:09:53,888
WELL, I'LL HELP IF I CAN,
BUT DON'T ASK ME TOO MUCH.

153
00:09:53,888 --> 00:09:54,922
ANASTASIA.

154
00:09:54,922 --> 00:09:57,055
NO! DON'T YOU CALL ME THAT!

155
00:09:57,055 --> 00:10:02,255
THERE ARE ONLY TWO PEOPLE
WHO CAN USE THAT NAME.

156
00:10:02,255 --> 00:10:04,922
SO, WHAT DO YOU WANT TO KNOW?

157
00:10:04,922 --> 00:10:09,288
MAO YENRAI,
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM?

158
00:10:10,855 --> 00:10:14,655
[MAN SINGING "AVE MARIA"]

159
00:10:19,188 --> 00:10:22,888
MAO TAIJIN,
WHAT'S THE REASON FOR THIS?

160
00:10:22,888 --> 00:10:26,122
NO NEED TO SPEAK,
MISS... VALENTINE.

161
00:10:26,122 --> 00:10:27,188
[GASPS]

162
00:10:27,188 --> 00:10:30,288
WE'VE DONE A VERY THOROUGH
BACKGROUND CHECK ON YOU.

163
00:10:30,288 --> 00:10:31,455
[GASPS]

164
00:10:31,455 --> 00:10:34,322
REST ASSURED, YOU'LL BE HELD
IN A VERY SECURE LOCATION.

165
00:10:34,322 --> 00:10:36,655
PLEASE, TAKE YOUR SEAT.

166
00:10:36,655 --> 00:10:38,655
OH.

167
00:10:58,122 --> 00:10:59,855
YOU'RE TREMBLING.

168
00:10:59,855 --> 00:11:02,255
WHO ARE YOU?

169
00:11:02,255 --> 00:11:03,988
TELL ME!

170
00:11:06,455 --> 00:11:07,822
VICIOUS.

171
00:11:31,797 --> 00:11:35,797
YOU KNOW, I DON'T
TELL YOU WHAT TO DO,

172
00:11:35,797 --> 00:11:39,777
BUT JUST DON'T GET TANGLED UP
WITH VICIOUS ANYMORE, RIGHT?

173
00:11:39,777 --> 00:11:40,518
WHY AM I TALKING TO YOU?

174
00:11:40,518 --> 00:11:41,552
IT'S USELESS.

175
00:11:41,552 --> 00:11:42,685
SORRY.

176
00:11:42,685 --> 00:11:46,118
YOU'VE NEVER LISTENED
TO ANYONE IN YOUR WHOLE LIFE.

177
00:11:49,718 --> 00:11:52,618
AND ON TOP OF THAT,
YOU'RE A STUBBORN SHOWOFF!

178
00:11:52,618 --> 00:11:53,418
YOU THINK IT'D KILL YOU

179
00:11:53,418 --> 00:11:55,252
TO LISTEN TO YOUR
ELDERS FOR ONCE?

180
00:11:55,252 --> 00:11:57,718
NO, THAT'S TOO MUCH TO ASK.

181
00:11:57,718 --> 00:12:02,352
ABOUT MAO, HE HAD A LOT
OF GUYS OUT LOOKING FOR YOU.

182
00:12:02,352 --> 00:12:04,518
HE WAS CONVINCED
YOU WERE STILL ALIVE

183
00:12:04,518 --> 00:12:05,618
SAID HE COULD FEEL IT.

184
00:12:05,618 --> 00:12:08,185
NO ONE COULD
TALK HIM OUT OF IT.

185
00:12:08,185 --> 00:12:12,552
SO NOW HERE YOU ARE,
FINALLY BACK, AND MAO IS...

186
00:12:12,552 --> 00:12:16,552
ANNIE, I THINK
YOU'VE HAD ENOUGH.

187
00:12:16,552 --> 00:12:17,385
NOT YET.

188
00:12:17,385 --> 00:12:20,085
THIS ONE'S FOR MAO.

189
00:12:20,085 --> 00:12:23,952
IF IT'S FOR MAO,
THEN I'LL DRINK IT MYSELF.

190
00:12:46,218 --> 00:12:47,985
ALL RIGHT, AND WHAT
ARE YOU PLANNING

191
00:12:47,985 --> 00:12:48,985
TO DO WITH
ALL THE ARTILLERY?

192
00:12:48,985 --> 00:12:50,685
WHERE'S THE GIRL?

193
00:12:50,685 --> 00:12:52,185
WHEN SHE SAW THE BOUNTY FIGURE,

194
00:12:52,185 --> 00:12:54,018
SHE HAD A LAPSE OF SANITY.

195
00:12:54,018 --> 00:12:55,318
I'M SURE SHE'S OUT SOMEWHERE

196
00:12:55,318 --> 00:12:57,652
SCREWING UP
AND GETTING IN TROUBLE.

197
00:12:57,652 --> 00:12:58,652
I SEE.

198
00:12:58,652 --> 00:12:59,718
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.

199
00:12:59,718 --> 00:13:02,152
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO GET
ANY REWARD MONEY FOR MAO.

200
00:13:02,152 --> 00:13:05,085
HE'S ALREADY DEAD... ASSASSINATED.

201
00:13:05,085 --> 00:13:09,352
INTERNAL POLITICS BETWEEN
RIVAL CRIME SYNDICATES,

202
00:13:09,352 --> 00:13:10,418
YOU UNDERSTAND?

203
00:13:10,418 --> 00:13:11,352
IT'S A TRAP!

204
00:13:11,352 --> 00:13:12,318
YEAH, I KNOW.

205
00:13:12,318 --> 00:13:14,185
I KNOW THE WHOLE SAD STORY.

206
00:13:14,185 --> 00:13:16,618
AND YOU'RE STILL GOING?

207
00:13:16,618 --> 00:13:19,152
WAIT. DOES THIS
HAVE TO DO WITH MAO?

208
00:13:19,152 --> 00:13:22,218
YEAH. I HAVE
A DEBT TO PAY OFF.

209
00:13:24,518 --> 00:13:27,518
YOU WANTED TO KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO MY ARM.

210
00:13:27,518 --> 00:13:28,418
HUH?

211
00:13:28,418 --> 00:13:29,618
THIS IS WHAT I PAID,

212
00:13:29,618 --> 00:13:33,185
YEAH, FOR BEING TOO GUNGHO
AND RUNNING AHEAD OF THE GAME.

213
00:13:33,185 --> 00:13:34,218
YOU GET THE POINT?

214
00:13:34,218 --> 00:13:36,285
I DON'T WANT
TO DO THIS, JET.

215
00:13:36,285 --> 00:13:37,285
THEN WHY ARE YOU?

216
00:13:37,285 --> 00:13:41,185
LET'S JUST SAY MY PAST
IS CATCHING UP TO ME.

217
00:13:42,352 --> 00:13:44,052
[BEEPING]

218
00:13:46,485 --> 00:13:48,552
I KIND OF GOT MYSELF CAUGHT.

219
00:13:48,552 --> 00:13:49,518
WHA--?

220
00:13:49,518 --> 00:13:51,385
YEAH. THEY WANT YOU
TO COME AND PICK ME UP.

221
00:13:51,385 --> 00:13:54,185
EITHER YOU SHOW UP
AT THE PLACE THEY SPECIFY,

222
00:13:54,185 --> 00:13:56,085
OR MY LIFE IS OVER.

223
00:13:56,085 --> 00:13:57,318
OH, THE ARRIVAL TIME IS--

224
00:13:57,318 --> 00:13:59,185
WHO ASKED YOU
TO GO OFF ON YOUR OWN?

225
00:13:59,185 --> 00:14:01,185
AW, COME ON, NOW!

226
00:14:01,185 --> 00:14:02,385
WE'RE COMRADES, RIGHT?

227
00:14:02,385 --> 00:14:05,652
YOU BROUGHT THIS ON YOURSELF,
SO DEAL WITH IT YOURSELF.

228
00:14:05,652 --> 00:14:06,752
WE'RE BUSY.

229
00:14:06,752 --> 00:14:07,752
NO! WAIT, JET!

230
00:14:07,752 --> 00:14:09,752
- HUH?
- WHERE ARE YOU?

231
00:14:09,752 --> 00:14:10,752
HUH?

232
00:14:10,752 --> 00:14:13,185
YOU MEAN YOU'RE REALLY
GOING TO COME FOR ME?

233
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:14,218
WELL, IT'S POSSIBLE.

234
00:14:14,218 --> 00:14:17,085
I'VE GOT MY REASONS,
SO DON'T TAKE IT PERSONAL.

235
00:14:17,085 --> 00:14:18,418
SPIKE!

236
00:14:25,718 --> 00:14:28,452
♪ I DON'T FEEL A THING ♪

237
00:14:28,452 --> 00:14:31,552
♪ AND I STOPPED REMEMBERING ♪

238
00:14:31,552 --> 00:14:39,118
♪ THE DAYS ARE JUST LIKE
MOMENTS TURNED TO HOURS ♪

239
00:14:39,118 --> 00:14:41,652
♪ MOTHER USED TO SAY ♪

240
00:14:41,652 --> 00:14:44,085
♪ IF YOU WANT,
YOU'LL FIND A WAY ♪

241
00:14:44,085 --> 00:14:52,118
♪ BUT MOTHER NEVER DANCED
THROUGH FIRE SHOWERS ♪

242
00:14:52,118 --> 00:14:58,052
♪ WALK IN THE RAIN ♪

243
00:14:58,052 --> 00:15:04,585
♪ IN THE RAIN ♪

244
00:15:04,585 --> 00:15:08,052
♪ I WALK IN THE RAIN ♪

245
00:15:08,052 --> 00:15:11,185
♪ IN THE RAIN ♪

246
00:15:11,185 --> 00:15:15,285
♪ IS IT RIGHT ♪

247
00:15:15,285 --> 00:15:20,152
♪ OR IS IT WRONG? ♪

248
00:15:20,152 --> 00:15:26,118
♪ AND IS IT HERE
THAT I BELONG? ♪

249
